{"title":"Kona Founders Purchased the Brand From Kent Outdoors","link":"https://theradavist.com/kona-founders-purchased-brand-from-kent-outdoors/","date":1716217316000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1422\" height=\"948\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Kona_Founders_Purchased_Brand_From_Kent_Outdoors.jpg?fit=1200,948&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Kona_Founders_Purchased_Brand_From_Kent_Outdoors.jpg?w=1422&amp;quality=75 1422w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Kona_Founders_Purchased_Brand_From_Kent_Outdoors.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Kona_Founders_Purchased_Brand_From_Kent_Outdoors.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;merchant_id=b826eaf3-114d-442c-83fc-42ed06e86479&amp;website_id=6ec3743b-a948-4c16-9d12-4b79ac107f25&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.konaworld.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kona Bicycles</a> went through a rough patch around Sea Otter classic <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/amidst-speculation-about-brand-kona-posts-on-instagram-this-morning/\" target=\"_blank\">and like we predicted</a>, the brand isn’t dead, in fact it was purchased from Kent Outdoors by its original founders, Dan Gerhard and Jake Heilbron. In 1988 Jake Heilbron, aka “Jake the Snake,” founded Kona Mountain Bikes with Dan Gerhard, so it’s amazing that the brand is returning to its roots. Read the full press release, written by the Kona team, below.</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2022/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-2.jpeg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/The-Kona-Sutra-ULTD-Touring-Bike-11.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Kona Bicycles has been in the news lately. We’d love to say that it’s because <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/kona-ouroboros-adventure-bike-first-look/\" target=\"_blank\">the new Ouroboros</a> is blowing everyone’s minds (because it really is that good), but truthfully, it has been a bumpy couple of years. So, it’s time to print a positive headline: Kona is returning home to its roots.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-8.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/10/KonaHonzoESD-63.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Kona’s founders, Dan Gerhard and Jake Heilbron have purchased the brand back from Kent Outdoors, and along with a team of dedicated, experienced Kona employees, are reuniting to keep the Long, Sweet Ride rolling. There are a lot of familiar faces here who you know from epic dealer launches, My Kona videos and trail days who are dedicated to the cause.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/11/Kyles-Swift-x-Kona-Rove-ST-Special-Edition-Touring-Bike-2.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Kona’s employees, dealers, and our dedicated customers have always been our strongest resource, and they keep on jamming to the beat of their own drum. With this return to being rider-owned and operated, we’re doubling down on our unique brand legacy and getting back to some basics.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1472\" height=\"981\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/12/morgan-taylor-kona-unit-basketpacker-29.jpg?fit=1200,981&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/12/morgan-taylor-kona-unit-basketpacker-29.jpg?w=1472&amp;quality=75 1472w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/12/morgan-taylor-kona-unit-basketpacker-29.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/12/morgan-taylor-kona-unit-basketpacker-29.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/12/morgan-taylor-kona-unit-basketpacker-29.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/12/morgan-taylor-kona-unit-basketpacker-29.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w\" /></p>\n<p>Renewing relationships with our nearly 1000-strong North American and European dealer network is our highest priority. Most of us started out in bike shops, and in our eyes, IBDs are our strongest advocates and allies. Healthy retailers are integral to making sure that Kona fans everywhere experience the ride of a lifetime. To best honor our dealer relationships, we are pausing D2C for all bikes. Konaworld will show changes to reflect this, and our social and communications channels will be getting reworked as well once we get things rolling. Bear with us, and we will keep you informed as we move through this transition.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-1.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-1.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-1.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-1.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>On the bike side, new Kona inventory is headed to our warehouse and distributors, and alongside the freshly released Ouroboros, we’ve got some incredible bikes in the pipeline that we are looking forward to unveiling. We’re beyond grateful for the support that our suppliers have shown us in this endeavor. Vendors like Fairly Bikes, who have been with us since our first bike in 1988, are a testament to the value of longstanding relationships where people take care of people.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-10.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-10.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-10.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-10.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Kona-Ouroboros-Adventure-Bike-First-Look-10.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>In more good news, we are now positioned to price our bikes much more competitively. Private ownership allows us to be more streamlined, more flexible, and quicker on our feet. This, combined with the support of our suppliers, means we can deliver high quality bikes in a distinctly Kona flavor at super attractive prices. We’ll never do a BOGO Sale again, so don’t ask, but we promise to offer good value for good money, always.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?fit=1200,1600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?resize=1024,819&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?resize=768,614&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?resize=1800,1440&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?resize=1335,1068&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?resize=700,560&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0571.jpg?resize=1536,1229&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1429\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?fit=1200,1429&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?resize=1024,732&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?resize=768,549&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?resize=1800,1286&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?resize=1335,954&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?resize=700,500&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/01/2021Kona153DL_Hindsley_DSCF0580.jpg?resize=1536,1097&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Our Pacific Northwest roots are as strong as ever. Offices in Ferndale, WA and North Vancouver, BC continue to anchor us proudly in place. Tenacious, resilient, straight talking, gritty and sometimes covered in grease, we are committed to keeping the distinctly Kona flavored bike buzz flowing, and helping people find freedom and fun. We are back. We are still here. Let’s ride.</p>\n<p>Welcome back to the smallest biggest bike company in the world.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>The Radavist endured <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/the-radavist-is-an-independent-website/\" target=\"_blank\">something similar last year</a> and we can assure you, this is never an easy process, so we’re stoked for our friends at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;merchant_id=b826eaf3-114d-442c-83fc-42ed06e86479&amp;website_id=6ec3743b-a948-4c16-9d12-4b79ac107f25&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.konaworld.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kona</a>, who have done such a great job at making solid bikes for so long. </em></p>\n<p><em>Check out some of our favorite Kona pieces from our archives below!</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/kona-founders-purchased-brand-from-kent-outdoors/\">Kona Founders Purchased the Brand From Kent Outdoors</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"96c28534ade6b0153d37d42e85f353379f24247d1b9469b4390ee54104e0836a","category":"Cycling"}